<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove boot from gear shift lever and secure assembly in vise with bottom of housing up.
                    Use a large screwdriver to twist between spring and housing, forcing spring from under lugs in the
                    housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302789">Figure 89</hotlnk>).
                    <emph type="bold">Do one coil at a time.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302789" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302789" filename="../figg13/G1302789.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 89. Force Spring From Under Lugs</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring, washer and gear shift lever from the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302790">Figure 90</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302790" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302790" filename="../figg13/G1302790.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Remove Tension Spring, Washer and Gear Shift Lever</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the spade pin from the bore in the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302791">Figure 91</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the O-ring from the groove
                    inside the tower.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302791" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302791" filename="../figg13/G1302791.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 91. Remove Spade Pin From Bore in Housing Tower</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
